      <body>
         <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>.
                    <lb n="2"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Adia">Adiae</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Celidon">Celidoni</name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="3"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen">
                     <gap reason="lost" atLeast="1" atMost="3" unit="character"/>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Valerius">
                     <unclear>V</unclear>alerius</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Telesphorus">
                     <expan><abbr>Telesph<hi rend="small">o</hi>r</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan>
                  </name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="4"/>
               <expan><abbr><unclear>c</unclear>oniug</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> optimae <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>e</ex><abbr>c</abbr><ex>it</ex></expan>.
                    <lb n="5"/>Vixit <expan><abbr>ann</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
               <num value="40">XL</num>, <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>ensibus</ex></expan>
               <num value="11">XI</num>, <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>iebus</ex></expan>
               <num value="17">XVII</num>.
                </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Dedicated to Adia Celidon by her husband Valerius Telesphor. She lived 40 years, 11 months, and 17 days.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>2) Adiae: name may be missing initital consonant F or T, with the former being more likely on the basis of name frequency. No other Adia Celidon is attested.</p>
            <p>3) A praenomen is almost certainly missing from the name of the dedicator.</p>
            <p>5) XVII: while possible that the number is larger, given the disposition if text on the stone, it need not be.</p>
            <p>Basis of verification: previous edition and photo</p>
         </div>
